* can aid in estimating expected returns based on the risk-free rate and market risk premium along with the individual assets' Beta.\n\n### Lessons for Quant_Diana\n1. **Diversification Strategy**: \n   - Incorporate a mix of these equities in the portfolio to balance risks. Analyzing their correlation can assist in selecting assets that complement each other.\n  \n2. **Regular Risk Assessment**:\n   - Continuously monitor the **market conditions** and how each equity performs against its risk profile.\n\n3. **Adaptability**:\n   - Be prepared to adapt the portfolio based on the prevailing market conditions and the evolving economic outlook, making use of the historical data to predict future movements.\n\n4. **Factor Analysis**:\n   - Investigate factors that might affect the performance of these stocks, such as sector performance, geopolitical risks, and broader economic indicators.\n\n### Conclusion\nA detailed analysis incorporating risk-return metrics will enhance the understanding of how to manage Strategic Alpha effectively for the equities in question. Utilizing quantitative methods in assessing the ongoing changes in risk profiles will be beneficial in maximizing potential returns.\n\n### References\n- [1] 13883872cc3cfa095f5bc5a9f79e8674.txt\n- [2] 7ea39fa671c1fff9a5c189e836bc1df6.txt\n- [3] 70e561701c91ea451921f856fa0df9d7.txt\n- [4] 1833d12976d2bb2b93bf254e19e70a71.txt\n- [5] 702007bf50d1007a06af7523f5198d79.txt. DNA: Пересмотр весовых коэффициентов в пользу лидеров роста (GMKN, VTBR) и сокращение доли в MOEX для минимизации корреляции с индексом в фазе стагнации.. Cash: 1100.914625. Portfolio: [{"s":"ROSN","q":3,"a":436.1},{"s":"GAZP","q":12,"a":125.625},{"s":"SBER","q":4,"a":324.49},{"s":"MOEX","q":8,"a":172.24},{"s":"GMKN","q":10,"a":136.12},{"s":"TATN","q":3,"a":576.766667},{"s":"VTBR","q":2,"a":95.665}]. History: 15:14 BUY TATN x1 @574.500000; 15:14 BUY VTBR x2 @95.665000; 15:14 SELL NVTK x1 @1171.900000. REGIME: {"regime":"risk_on","risk":"GREEN","