2	2026-04-22 21:30:29.490862+00	ai_genetic_incubator	\N	Strategy alpha 2026-04-23	I will begin by exploring the codebase to understand the existing strategy frameworks and technical indicator implementations, which will help me tailor the Alpha Cheat Sheet to the project's current architecture. \n\nI will check for the presence of `GEMINI.md` and any other configuration files in the parent directory to ensure I adhere to the foundational mandates and project-specific guidelines.\n\n### Strategy Architect Report: MOEX Asset Intelligence\n\n**Date:** April 23, 2026  \n**Analyst:** Lead Strategy Architect & Data Scientist  \n**Scope:** MOEX High-Liquidity Basket Analysis\n\n---\n\n### 1. Market Sentiment Overview\nThe analyzed session shows a mixed market with a slight bearish tilt in high-growth names (VTBR, OZON) and resilience in core financials and commodities (SBER, MOEX, ROSN). \n\n- **Macro Sentiment (USD/Gold):** Both USD (+0.16%) and Gold (+0.19%) are trending upwards but currently trading near the bottom of their intraday ranges. This suggests a **bullish accumulation** phase where pullbacks are being bought.\n- **Internal Strength:** **SBER** and **MOEX** are the clear leaders, both closing at or near the absolute high of the 11-bar range, indicating strong demand-side momentum.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Alpha Cheat Sheet: Asset-Specific Rules\n\n| Ticker | Setup Type | Execution Rule | Key Level |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **SBER** | **High-Close Breakout** | Enter Long if `price > 326.94` with trailing stop at `324.50`. | 326.94 |\n| **VTBR** | **Range Reversion** | Mean reversion buy if `price < 94.00`, targeting `96.00`. Avoid shorts below `93.50`. | 94.66 |\n| **NVTK** | **Relative Strength** | Buy on dips to `1190.00`. Closing above `1210.00` confirms trend continuation. | 1206.10 |\n| **GLDRUB**| **Support Bounce** | Long accumulation between `11400` and `11420`. Stop loss at `11380`. | 11423.6 |\n| **USD000**| **USD/RUB Floor** | Buy USD if `price < 74.60` with target `76.50` (mid-range). | 74.66 |\n| **ROSN** | **Momentum Lead** | Follow trend if `price > 436.50`. High is `481.75` (10% range overhead). | 436.55 |\n| **OZON** | **Vol-Contraction** | Neutral. Wait for breakout of `[4362 - 4489]` range. Short bias below `4450`. | 4473.5 |\n| **MAGN** | **Sector Lag** | Short if `price < 27.50`. MAGN shows persistent weakness vs LNLK/CHMF. | 27.64 |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Recurring Profitable Setups\n\n#### A. The "Clean Close" (Momentum)\n- **Observed in:** SBER, MOEX, ROSN.\n- **Pattern:** Last price equals or exceeds 95% of the range (High-Low).\n- **Rule:** If `(Last - Low) / (High - Low) > 0.95`, enter Long at the open of the next bar for a 3-bar momentum play.\n\n#### B. The "Spring Back" (Mean Reversion)\n- **Observed in:** GLDRUB_TOM, USD000UTSTOM.\n- **Pattern:** Asset is positive (`change_pct > 0.1%`) but trading in the lower 15% of the intraday range.\n- **Rule:** If `Change > 0` AND `Position in Range < 0.15`, Buy for a move back to the range median.\n\n#### C. High-Beta Exhaustion (Short)\n- **Observed in:** VTBR.\n- **Pattern:** Large range expansion (High-Low > 10%) with a negative close.\n- **Rule:** If `Range / Price > 0.10` AND `Change < -0.5%`, look for a secondary flush before any long entry. Avoid catching the falling knife.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Strategic Recommendations\n1. **Long Exposure:** Focus on **SBER** and **GMKN**. These assets exhibit "Hard Momentum" where supply is completely absorbed at local highs.\n2. **Hedge/Safety:** Accumulate **GLDRUB_TOM**. The positive change combined with its proximity to the low (11382) offers an asymmetric R/R (Risk/Reward) for a flight-to-safety move.\n3. **Risk Warning:** **VTBR** and **PIKK** exhibit extreme volatility (ranges > 10%). Reduce position sizing by 50% for these tickers as per **Storm Mode** guidelines in `GEMINI.md`.	PROPOSED	PENDING	\N	\N	{"kind": "alpha_cheat_sheet", "auto_promote": false}
